Parliament, Thursday 27 May 2021 – The National Council of Provinces (NCOP) and the National Assembly (NA) will tomorrow, Friday, 28 May, hold a joint hybrid plenary sitting to debate the 25th Anniversary of the Constitution of the Republic of South Africa.
	
	Joint Rule 7(2) of the Joint Rules of Parliament, allows for both the Speaker of the National Assembly, Ms Thandi Modise, and the Chairperson of the National Council of Provinces, Mr Amos Masondo to call for a hybrid or virtual joint sitting of the two Houses of Parliament to conduct a debate on matters of national public importance.
	
	DETAILS OF THE NCOP AND NA JOINT HYBRID PLENARY SITTING:
	
	Date: Friday, 28 May 2021
	Time: 10:00 – 18:30
	Venue: National Assembly Chamber and virtual platforms
	
	
	Important to note:
	
	Members of the media who wish to physically attend the NCOP and NA hybrid plenary sitting should send their details (full name, media house, ID or passport number) to Manelisi Ntsodo on email: mntsodo@parliament.gov.za by no later than 9am TOMORROW, Friday, 28 May.
	
	Parliamentary meetings are open to the media and the public. Journalists who are interested in covering these meetings (including receiving links to virtual meetings) are requested to forward their contact details to Mlindi Mpindi on email mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliamentary Communications Services WhatsApp Group, where such information is shared. Journalists must forward these requests using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow committee and House sittings live on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament’s YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
